Key Match Events: Jack Grealish scored in the 18th minute.
Trent Alexander-Arnold scored in the 74th minute.
Declan Rice scored in the 84th minute.
Hoskonen scored for Finland in the 87th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: England are facing a nervous wait over two of their most integral attackers ahead of Sunday's UEFA Nations League clash with Finland in Helsinki.
Captain Harry Kane missed the previous match with a knock sustained while on duty for Bayern Munich.
Arsenal winger Bukayo Saka was brought off early in the second half with a leg issue, likely a hamstring problem.
Jack Grealish also has a fitness problem, so Jude Bellingham, Anthony Gordon, and Cole Palmer could hold their places.
Carsley may bring in either Ollie Watkins or Dominic Solanke if Kane is not fit enough to start.
Conor Gallagher in midfield would offer a stable presence alongside Declan Rice.
John Stones may cede his place to Marc Guehi, while Kyle Walker could be a straight swap for Trent Alexander-Arnold on the right.
